               <msContents>
                  <summary>Gospel of John.  F<locus target="#1r"/>-108v: , arranged by the original hand for the days of the week: Saturday (<locus target="#22v"/>), Wednesday (a note on <locus target="#57r"/> that says, "here ends [the readings] of Wednesday [and] of Saturday, ተፈጸመ ዘረቡዕ ዘቀዳሚት), Wednesday (<locus target="#57v"/>), Thursday (<locus target="#70v"/>).  Also arranged for the days of the week  by a secondary hand: Saturday (<locus target="#48r"/>), Friday (<locus target="#88v"/>), Sunday (<locus target="#98v"/>). The mal' (መልዓ) appears on <locus target="#108v"/>. <locus target="#109rv"/>: Calendar of the feast days of the martyrs and disciples. The illuminations and harags look authentic.</summary>
